5

00:00:13,040 --> 00:00:16,200

Artificial intelligence is a field of computer science


6

00:00:16,200 --> 00:00:21,160

which is engaged in the creation of programs and systems capable of performing tasks,


7

00:00:21,160 --> 00:00:25,040

which usually require human intellectual abilities.


8

00:00:25,040 --> 00:00:28,120

These tasks may include pattern recognition,


9

00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:32,360

natural language processing, planning and decision making.


10

00:00:32,360 --> 00:00:37,240

Artificial intelligence uses methods of machine learning, deep learning,


11

00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:42,520

neural networks and other technologies for data analysis and model creation,


12

00:00:42,520 --> 00:00:46,120

which can imitate human thinking.


13

00:00:46,120 --> 00:00:49,200

The term "artificial intelligence" was coined by John McCarthy


14

00:00:49,200 --> 00:00:54,160

at the Dartmouth Conference back in 1956.


15

00:00:54,160 --> 00:00:57,320

Development of artificial intelligence over the past 70 years


16

00:00:57,320 --> 00:01:00,160

can be divided into several stages.


17

00:01:00,160 --> 00:01:06,080

At the first stages, systems were created
using logical databases and rules.


18

00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:09,240

The second stage began with the advent of machine learning,


19

00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:11,880

At this stage, algorithms were developed


20

00:01:11,880 --> 00:01:16,840

allowing computers to learn from experience and make predictions.


21

00:01:16,840 --> 00:01:21,440

This was followed by the stage of development of deep learning and neural networks,


22

00:01:21,440 --> 00:01:25,840

At this stage, deep learning models were created.


23

00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,360

History of the emergence of large language models


24

00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:33,440

begins with the development of simpler models in the 80s and 90s.


25

00:01:33,440 --> 00:01:40,040

However, a real breakthrough in this area
occurred in the late 2010s with the advent of technology


26

00:01:40,040 --> 00:01:40,706

generative pre-trained transformers - such as neural language models,


27

00:01:40,706 --> 00:01:51,000

which are trained on large datasets to generate human-like text.


28

00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:55,600

Currently, the ongoing development and improvement of artificial


29

00:01:55,600 --> 00:01:57,880

intelligence includes deep learning,


30

00:01:57,880 --> 00:02:02,200

natural language processing and computer vision.


31

00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:05,160

There are two types of artificial intelligence:


32

00:02:05,160 --> 00:02:09,160

strong (or general) and weak (or specialized).


33

00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:13,000

Examples of weak artificial intelligence are smart home technologies,


34

00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:17,400

online translators, image recognition systems, and so on.


35

00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:23,040

Weak artificial intelligence is capable of solving only those tasks for which it was created and trained.


36

00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:26,520

For example, a chess program can only play chess.


37

00:02:26,520 --> 00:02:30,440

What distinguishes strong artificial intelligence from weak artificial intelligence is its ability to decide


38

00:02:30,440 --> 00:02:33,560

various tasks, rather than highly specialized ones.


39

00:02:33,560 --> 00:02:37,280

At the moment there is no strong artificial intelligence,


40

00:02:37,280 --> 00:02:40,840

which would be capable of solving a wide range of problems.


41

00:02:40,840 --> 00:02:46,040

Scientists and experts argue about the possibilities and timing of creating artificial intelligence,


42

00:02:46,040 --> 00:02:50,560

representing the integration of already created artificial intelligence systems


43

00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:56,200

into a single system capable
solve humanity's problems.


44

00:02:56,200 --> 00:02:59,120

Rapid development of artificial intelligence technologies


45

00:02:59,120 --> 00:03:02,520

requires control by society and the state.


46

