leadership of our country in the global high-tech market.


52

00:03:26,680 --> 00:03:31,160

The use of artificial intelligence in science and industry is developing dynamically


53

00:03:31,160 --> 00:03:34,640

and covers all new areas of human life.


54

00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:39,040

This rapid spread of technology causes concern among citizens,


55

00:03:39,040 --> 00:03:42,160

how safe is artificial intelligence for humans,


56

00:03:42,160 --> 00:03:44,720

in which areas it is permissible to use it,


57

00:03:44,720 --> 00:03:50,360

who will be responsible for the actions of artificial intelligence, etc.


58

00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:56,160

Large language models can be used for scientific purposes to solve various problems.


59

00:03:56,160 --> 00:04:00,600

For example, they can be used
for processing large volumes of text data -


60

00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:04,720

such as analysis of scientific articles, patents or medical records.


61

00:04:04,720 --> 00:04:08,400

They can also help in sentiment analysis of the text,


62

00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:12,960

identifying keywords and phrases, as well as identifying plagiarism.


63

00:04:12,960 --> 00:04:20,120

The model in its work receives a “prompt” as input - this is a request from the user or a set of keywords,


64

00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:24,480

and then selects the most suitable next word,


65

00:04:24,480 --> 00:04:28,360

after that, the resulting string is again fed to the input of the model,


66

00:04:28,360 --> 00:04:32,400

and she selects another word.


67

00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:36,760

Using prompts to write texts allows graduate students to better


68

00:04:36,760 --> 00:04:40,880

understand the unique challenges associated with writing scientific papers,


69

00:04:40,880 --> 00:04:45,880

and develop the skills necessary to work effectively in this field.


70

00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,400

It should be noted, however,


71

00:04:48,400 --> 00:04:53,680

that one should always use the most modern and advanced technologies available


72

00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:57,400

for you the moment you use them.


73

00:04:57,400 --> 00:05:01,520

There are many different types of prompts,


74

00:05:01,520 --> 00:05:06,880

which can be applied regardless of which language model you are using.


75

00:05:06,880 --> 00:05:13,800

The basic principle is to always start a query with an action verb, for example, “come up with options”


76

00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:16,440

“write”, “analyze” and so on.


77

00:05:16,440 --> 00:05:22,240

Clearly formulate the end goal - the type of content, for example, an analytical article,


78

00:05:22,240 --> 00:05:26,400

description of the schedule or email and subject matter.


79

00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:29,520

You can create complex three-step tasks,


80

00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:34,840

including collecting information, summarizing and creating a final answer.


81

00:05:34,840 --> 00:05:39,840

You can also specify the length of the text (for example, from 400 to 800 characters).


82

00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:46,600

If you don't want to go into detail,
you can simply write: short or long text.


83

00:05:46,600 --> 00:05:50,880

There are several types of scientific tasks that can be automated


84

00:05:50,880 --> 00:05:54,920

using artificial intelligence. For example, classification of articles.


85

00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:57,520

Artificial intelligence can categorize articles


86

00:05:57,520 --> 00:06:03,120

according to various categories such as topic, type of study, year of publication, and so on.


87

00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:07,000

Text analysis: artificial intelligence can analyze the text of an article,


88

00:06:07,000 --> 00:06:12,040

identifying key words, phrases and ideas and their relationships.


89

00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:15,760

Identification of authors: artificial intelligence can determine the authors of an article,


90

00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:19,200

by comparing their writing style to other authors in the database.


91

00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:23,760

Article quality assessment: artificial intelligence can evaluate the quality of the article itself,


92

00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:28,080

analyzing its structure, research quality and results.


93

00:06:28,080 --> 00:06:31,320

